cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper discusses the impact of GDPR on online advertising ecosystem, which involves data privacy and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also evaluates the right to data portability, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). The analysis of the connections between third-parties and the impact of GDPR on the number of connections can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper also discusses the implications for online tracking companies, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
